  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IDPs</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of this project is to contribute towards the food security of internally displaced people, host communities in villages and camps by providing essential non-food items and seeds and increasing households access to income.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Concern shifted its programming to an emergency focus in Masisi in 2008 due to the changing needs, security and access. Concern has used vouchers as an alternative to distributing non-food item kits. Since that time, cash-based activities have continued to be a central component of Concern&#x2019;s emergency programming in Masisi. Concern has made modifications along the way based on lessons and evaluations, as well as the desire to try new approaches that might be more effective and appropriate 
Target beneficiaries : IDP camps and host families 
The main activities include: 
&#x2022; distribution of essential NFIs 
&#x2022; Improving in access to markets by rehabilitating roads and bridges 
&#x2022; Improve beneficiaries&#x2019; access to income through the creation of cash-for-work employment opportunity and unconditional cash transfers.</narrative>
  </description>
